    <main class="flex-1 h-full overflow-y-auto relative scroll-smooth w-full">
        
        <!-- Mobile Header -->
        <div class="md:hidden glass border-b border-organic-700/50 p-4 sticky top-0 z-40 flex justify-between items-center">
            <div class="flex items-center space-x-2">
                <i data-lucide="leaf" class="text-organic-400 w-5 h-5"></i>
                <span class="font-serif text-white font-bold">Superbloom</span>
            </div>
            <select onchange="navTo(this.value)" class="bg-slate-800 text-slate-200 border border-slate-600 rounded p-1 font-mono text-xs focus:ring-organic-500">
                <option value="home">/home</option>
                <option value="why">/why_here</option>
                <option value="overview">/overview</option>
                <option value="reflections">/reflections</option>
                <option value="quotes">/quotes</option>
                <option value="next">/next_session</option>
                <option value="pl">AI Professional Learning</option>
            </select>
        </div>

        <!-- Part 1: Hero / Title Page -->
        <section id="home" class="page-section min-h-screen flex flex-col justify-center py-16">
            <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center reveal">
                
                <h1 class="text-6xl md:text-8xl lg:text-[7rem] font-serif font-bold text-white mb-8 leading-tight">
                    The Endangered <br/>
                    <span class="text-transparent bg-clip-text bg-gradient-to-r from-organic-400 to-digital-400 glitch-hover transition-all cursor-default pb-4 inline-block">Resource</span>
                </h1>
                
                <p class="text-2xl md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-sans text-slate-300 mb-12 max-w-5xl mx-auto leading-normal">
                    Navigating the Attention Economy in K-12 Education
                </p>
                
                <div class="glass-card rounded-3xl p-10 lg:p-14 max-w-3xl mx-auto border-t-4 border-t-organic-500 relative overflow-hidden shadow-2xl">
                    <div class="absolute -right-10 -top-10 opacity-10">
                        <i data-lucide="book-open" class="w-64 h-64"></i>
                    </div>
                    <h2 class="text-4xl lg:text-6xl font-serif text-white mb-4 relative z-10">Superbloom</h2>
                    <p class="text-xl lg:text-3xl text-slate-400 font-sans mb-10 relative z-10">by Nicholas Carr</p>
                    <div class="inline-block bg-organic-900 border border-organic-700 rounded-xl px-8 py-4 font-mono text-xl lg:text-2xl text-organic-400 relative z-10 shadow-[0_0_15px_rgba(34,197,94,0.15)]">
                        Part 1: Collapse <span class="text-slate-500 ml-4">Pages 1-78</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Part 2: Why We're Here -->
        <section id="why" class="page-section hidden min-h-screen py-20 relative border-t border-slate-800">
            <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 w-full">
                <div class="text-center mb-16 reveal">
                    <h2 class="text-3xl font-serif text-white mb-4">Why We're Here</h2>
                    <div class="w-24 h-1 bg-gradient-to-r from-organic-500 to-transparent mx-auto rounded"></div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
                    <!-- Reason A -->
                    <div class="glass-card p-8 rounded-xl reveal delay-100 flex flex-col items-center text-center group">
                        <div class="w-16 h-16 rounded-full bg-slate-800 flex items-center justify-center mb-6 group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform border border-slate-700">
                            <i data-lucide="users" class="text-organic-400 w-8 h-8"></i>
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="font-mono text-lg text-white mb-3">&gt; Adult Conversations</h3>
                        <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                            We need dedicated space for high-level, adult conversations among K-12 educators to process complex pedagogical shifts.
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Reason B -->
                    <div class="glass-card p-8 rounded-xl reveal delay-200 flex flex-col items-center text-center group">
                        <div class="w-16 h-16 rounded-full bg-slate-800 flex items-center justify-center mb-6 group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform border border-slate-700">
                            <i data-lucide="globe" class="text-digital-400 w-8 h-8"></i>
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="font-mono text-lg text-white mb-3">&gt; Understand the World</h3>
                        <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                            We must deeply comprehend the attention economy and the hyper-connected, algorithmic world we have created for our students.
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Reason C -->
                    <div class="glass-card p-8 rounded-xl reveal delay-300 flex flex-col items-center text-center group">
                        <div class="w-16 h-16 rounded-full bg-slate-800 flex items-center justify-center mb-6 group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform border border-slate-700">
                            <i data-lucide="compass" class="text-organic-400 w-8 h-8"></i>
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="font-mono text-lg text-white mb-3">&gt; Navigate the Future</h3>
                        <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                            Equipped with understanding, we need to develop strategies to help our students effectively navigate and thrive in that world.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Part 3: Overview -->
        <section id="overview" class="page-section hidden min-h-screen py-20 bg-slate-900/50 relative border-y border-slate-800">
            <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 reveal w-full">
                <div class="flex items-center space-x-4 mb-8">
                    <i data-lucide="book-open-check" class="text-digital-400 w-8 h-8"></i>
                    <h2 class="text-3xl font-serif text-white">Overview: Part 1</h2>
                </div>
                
                <div class="pl-6 border-l-2 border-digital-500/50 relative">
                    <div class="absolute -left-[9px] top-0 w-4 h-4 rounded-full bg-digital-900 border-2 border-digital-400"></div>
                    <p class="text-lg text-slate-300 leading-relaxed font-serif italic mb-6">
                        In "Collapse," Carr traces the history of communication technologies to argue that each new medium doesn't simply transmit information; it reshapes how societies think, relate, and organize.
                    </p>
                    <p class="text-lg text-slate-300 leading-relaxed font-serif">
                        He shows how the acceleration and mechanization of communication has steadily eroded what he calls "human scale," culminating in the algorithmic feed, which replaced personal agency with machine agency and turned communication's essential function from transport into <span class="text-digital-400 font-semibold border-b border-digital-400/50 pb-0.5">manipulation</span>.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Part 4: Reflection Questions -->
        <section id="reflections" class="page-section hidden min-h-screen py-20 relative">
            <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 w-full">
                <div class="mb-12 reveal">
                    <h2 class="text-3xl font-serif text-white mb-2">Reflection Questions</h2>
                    <p class="font-mono text-slate-500 text-sm">Please consider the following as you read:</p>
                </div>

                <div class="space-y-6">
                    <!-- Q1 -->
                    <div class="glass-card p-6 rounded-lg reveal flex gap-4 items-start group">
                        <div class="font-mono text-organic-400 text-xl font-bold mt-1 opacity-50 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity">01</div>
                        <div>
                            <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed font-sans">
                                Carr argues that analog media's "messiness" (its physicality, fragmentation, and inefficiency) actually protected our capacity to make sense of information. <strong class="text-white font-medium">What parallel "messiness" exists in classroom learning, and what happens when we optimize it away?</strong>
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Q2 -->
                    <div class="glass-card p-6 rounded-lg reveal flex gap-4 items-start group">
                        <div class="font-mono text-digital-400 text-xl font-bold mt-1 opacity-50 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity">02</div>
                        <div>
                            <div class="bg-slate-900/80 border border-slate-700 p-4 rounded mb-4 font-serif text-sm italic text-slate-400">
                                "The feed removed human deliberation and judgement from the process. It replaced personal agency with machine agency" <span class="font-mono text-xs">(p. 64)</span>.
                            </div>
                            <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed font-sans">
                                <strong class="text-white font-medium">Where do you see this replacement of human judgment with algorithmic or automated decision-making showing up in education</strong>, whether in the tools we adopt, the platforms students use, or the systems that shape what content reaches learners?
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Q3 -->
                    <div class="glass-card p-6 rounded-lg reveal flex gap-4 items-start group">
                        <div class="font-mono text-organic-400 text-xl font-bold mt-1 opacity-50 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity">03</div>
                        <div>
                            <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed font-sans">
                                Carr writes that "communication is a moral force" (p. 19). If that's true, <strong class="text-white font-medium">what moral responsibilities do educators carry as they choose and mediate the communication technologies used in their classrooms?</strong>
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Q4 -->
                    <div class="glass-card p-6 rounded-lg reveal flex gap-4 items-start group">
                        <div class="font-mono text-digital-400 text-xl font-bold mt-1 opacity-50 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity">04</div>
                        <div>
                            <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed font-sans">
                                Part 1 documents a recurring historical pattern: each new communication technology is greeted with utopian promises before its destabilizing effects become visible. <strong class="text-white font-medium">How should this pattern inform how school divisions evaluate and adopt emerging technologies, including AI?</strong>
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Q5 -->
                    <div class="glass-card p-6 rounded-lg reveal flex gap-4 items-start group">
                        <div class="font-mono text-organic-400 text-xl font-bold mt-1 opacity-50 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity">05</div>
                        <div>
                            <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed font-sans">
                                Carr contends that algorithms "influence meaning both directly (by selecting the information people see) and indirectly (by promoting certain forms of expression and discouraging others)" (p. 78). <strong class="text-white font-medium">How might this dynamic be shaping the reading, writing, and thinking habits of students, even outside of school?</strong>
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Part 5: Key Quotes -->
        <section id="quotes" class="page-section hidden min-h-screen py-20 bg-slate-900/30 relative border-t border-slate-800">
            <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 w-full">
                <div class="flex justify-between items-end mb-12 reveal">
                    <div>
                        <h2 class="text-3xl font-serif text-white mb-2 flex items-center gap-3">
                            <i data-lucide="message-square-quote" class="text-organic-400"></i>
                            Key Quotes
                        </h2>
                        <p class="font-mono text-slate-500 text-sm">Extracted from Collapse (pg. 1-78)</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="columns-1 md:columns-2 lg:columns-3 gap-6 space-y-6">
                    
                    <!-- Quote Cards (Populated systematically) -->
                    <div class="break-inside-avoid glass-card p-6 rounded-xl relative group reveal hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all cursor-pointer ring-2 ring-transparent hover:ring-digital-500/50 hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-digital-500/20" onclick="openQuoteModal(this)">
                        <div class="absolute top-4 right-4 font-mono text-xs text-organic-500 bg-organic-900/50 px-2 py-1 rounded">p. 8</div>
                        <p class="font-serif text-slate-300 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">"Whenever the “mechanisms of communication” change, society changes. The faster the mechanisms change, the faster society changes."</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="break-inside-avoid glass-card p-6 rounded-xl relative group reveal hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all cursor-pointer ring-2 ring-transparent hover:ring-digital-500/50 hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-digital-500/20 border-l-2 border-l-digital-500" onclick="openQuoteModal(this)">
                        <div class="absolute top-4 right-4 font-mono text-xs text-digital-500 bg-digital-900/50 px-2 py-1 rounded">p. 9</div>
                        <p class="font-serif text-slate-300 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">"Every new medium creates a new environment."</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="break-inside-avoid glass-card p-6 rounded-xl relative group reveal hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all cursor-pointer ring-2 ring-transparent hover:ring-digital-500/50 hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-digital-500/20" onclick="openQuoteModal(this)">
                        <div class="absolute top-4 right-4 font-mono text-xs text-organic-500 bg-organic-900/50 px-2 py-1 rounded">p. 11</div>
                        <p class="font-serif text-slate-300 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">"Every communication medium is political, a conduit of power as much as thought."</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="break-inside-avoid glass-card p-6 rounded-xl relative group reveal hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all cursor-pointer ring-2 ring-transparent hover:ring-digital-500/50 hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-digital-500/20" onclick="openQuoteModal(this)">
                        <div class="absolute top-4 right-4 font-mono text-xs text-organic-500 bg-organic-900/50 px-2 py-1 rounded">p. 13</div>
                        <p class="font-serif text-slate-300 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">"As communication speeds up, once-stable social structures and relations become as malleable as water."</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="break-inside-avoid glass-card p-6 rounded-xl relative group reveal hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all cursor-pointer ring-2 ring-transparent hover:ring-digital-500/50 hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-digital-500/20" onclick="openQuoteModal(this)">
                        <div class="absolute top-4 right-4 font-mono text-xs text-organic-500 bg-organic-900/50 px-2 py-1 rounded">p. 18</div>
                        <p class="font-serif text-slate-300 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">"Human beings are not computers. The communities they form are not electronic networks. Society does not scale."</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="break-inside-avoid glass-card p-6 rounded-xl relative group reveal hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all cursor-pointer ring-2 ring-transparent hover:ring-digital-500/50 hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-digital-500/20 border-l-2 border-l-digital-500" onclick="openQuoteModal(this)">
                        <div class="absolute top-4 right-4 font-mono text-xs text-digital-500 bg-digital-900/50 px-2 py-1 rounded">p. 18</div>
                        <p class="font-serif text-slate-300 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">"Networked computers communicate with a cold and predictable precision. People communicate with love, anger, passion, resentment, joy, and fear…"</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="break-inside-avoid glass-card p-6 rounded-xl relative group reveal hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all cursor-pointer ring-2 ring-transparent hover:ring-digital-500/50 hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-digital-500/20" onclick="openQuoteModal(this)">
                        <div class="absolute top-4 right-4 font-mono text-xs text-organic-500 bg-organic-900/50 px-2 py-1 rounded">p. 19</div>
                        <p class="font-serif text-slate-300 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">"Communication is a moral force."</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="break-inside-avoid glass-card p-6 rounded-xl relative group reveal hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all cursor-pointer ring-2 ring-transparent hover:ring-digital-500/50 hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-digital-500/20" onclick="openQuoteModal(this)">
                        <div class="absolute top-4 right-4 font-mono text-xs text-organic-500 bg-organic-900/50 px-2 py-1 rounded">p. 46</div>
                        <p class="font-serif text-slate-300 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">"To control a nation’s soundtrack was to be always inside its citizens’ heads."</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="break-inside-avoid glass-card p-6 rounded-xl relative group reveal hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all cursor-pointer ring-2 ring-transparent hover:ring-digital-500/50 hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-digital-500/20" onclick="openQuoteModal(this)">
                        <div class="absolute top-4 right-4 font-mono text-xs text-organic-500 bg-organic-900/50 px-2 py-1 rounded">p. 54</div>
                        <p class="font-serif text-slate-300 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">"Like the legal and regulatory system that surrounded it, the analog media system was imperfect, but its very messiness helped maintain communication’s human scale. Its physicality and fragmentation prevented the speed and volume of electronic networks from overwhelming people’s sense-making capacities."</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="break-inside-avoid glass-card p-6 rounded-xl relative group reveal hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all cursor-pointer ring-2 ring-transparent hover:ring-digital-500/50 hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-digital-500/20 border-l-2 border-l-digital-500" onclick="openQuoteModal(this)">
                        <div class="absolute top-4 right-4 font-mono text-xs text-digital-500 bg-digital-900/50 px-2 py-1 rounded">p. 61</div>
                        <p class="font-serif text-slate-300 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">"On the internet, the wiretap wouldn’t be a bug; it would be a feature."</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="break-inside-avoid glass-card p-6 rounded-xl relative group reveal hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all cursor-pointer ring-2 ring-transparent hover:ring-digital-500/50 hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-digital-500/20" onclick="openQuoteModal(this)">
                        <div class="absolute top-4 right-4 font-mono text-xs text-organic-500 bg-organic-900/50 px-2 py-1 rounded">p. 63</div>
                        <p class="font-serif text-slate-300 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">"With digitization, communication has lost its human scale."</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="break-inside-avoid glass-card p-6 rounded-xl relative group reveal hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all cursor-pointer ring-2 ring-transparent hover:ring-digital-500/50 hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-digital-500/20" onclick="openQuoteModal(this)">
                        <div class="absolute top-4 right-4 font-mono text-xs text-organic-500 bg-organic-900/50 px-2 py-1 rounded">p. 68</div>
                        <p class="font-serif text-slate-300 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">"The essential function of the mechanism of communication wasn’t transport anymore. It was manipulation—manipulation of information and by extension manipulation of those receiving the information."</p>
                    </div>

